metadata.title: ##### Introduction
metadata.content:
OpenAI Model
Configure OpenAI as your model provider
The
```
openai
```
function configures OpenAI as your model provider.
Copy Ask AI
```
import { createAgent , openai } from "@inngest/agent-kit" ;

const agent = createAgent ({
name: "Code writer" ,
system: "You are an expert TypeScript programmer." ,
model: openai ({ model: "gpt-4" }),
});
```

metadata.title: ##### Introduction
##### Introduction
metadata.content:
OpenAI Model
Configuration
Options
model string required ID of the model to use. See the
[model endpoint](https://platform.openai.com/docs/models#model-endpoint-compatibility)
[compatibility](https://platform.openai.com/docs/models#model-endpoint-compatibility)
table for details on which models work with the Chat API.
apiKey string The OpenAI API key to use for authenticating your request. By default we'll
search for and use the
```
OPENAI_API_KEY
```
environment variable.
baseUrl string default: "https://api.openai.com/v1/" The base URL for the OpenAI API.
defaultParameters object The default parameters to use for the model (ex:
```
temperature
```
,
```
max_tokens
```
,
etc).
